December 2nd, 2024 – Nativity Diorama

This challenge showed four close-up images of a very detailed nativity scene diorama. The pictures included:
-Small village buildings
-People figurines
-Animals
-A miniature Roman-style structure
-A stable with the nativity

At first glance, the scene looked extremely elaborate, much larger than a typical nativity display.

Step 1 – Reverse Image Search
To identify the specific diorama, I performed a reverse image search on one of the images. The results pointed toward large-scale nativity displays, often called “presepi.”
These displays are especially common in Italy.

Step 2 – Identify the Specific Display
Looking more closely at the images, I noticed one structure that resembled a miniature Roman Colosseum-style building with illuminated arches. That detail helped narrow the search.
I searched:

large Italian nativity scene with Roman colosseum miniature
largest nativity scene diorama Italy
This led me to information about a massive nativity scene installation that gets updated yearly.

Step 3 – Find the 2023 Set Piece Count

The challenge asked:

According to the official count, how many pieces were used (at least) in the 2023 set?
Once I located the official website and articles describing the display, I found the official piece count for the 2023 installation.
The listed minimum number of pieces used in the set was:

5800

Final Answer

5800
